Patients Despite Highly Active Antiretroviral Therapy\n| journal =  Open Forum Infect Diseases\n| date = December 2015\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1128/JVI.01044-15\n| pmid = 25995256\n| issn = \n| volume = 89\n| issue = 15\n| pages = 8096\u20138100\n| last = Griffin\n| first = Daniel\n| first2=Stephen P. |last2=Goff\n| title = HIV-1 Is Restricted prior to Integration of Viral DNA in Primary Cord-Derived Human CD34+ Cells\n| journal =  [[Journal of Virology]]\n| date = May 2015\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.2119/molmed.2012.00203\n| pmid = 22634719\n| issn = \n| volume = 18\n| issue = 1\n| pages = 1003\u20131008\n| last = Griffin\n| first = Daniel\n| first2=Thomas L. |last2=Rothstein\n| title = Human \u201cOrchestrator\u201d CD11b+ B1 Cells Spontaneously Secrete Interleukin-10 and Regulate T-Cell Activity\n| journal =  Molecular Medicine\n| date = May 2012\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2012.00122\n| pmid = 22654880\n| issn = \n| volume = \n| issue = \n| pages = \n| last = Griffin\n| first = Daniel\n| first2=Thomas L. |last2=Rothstein\n| title = Human b1 cell frequency: isolation and analysis of human b1 cells\n| journal =  Frontiers in immunology\n| date = May 2012\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1084/jem.20110978\n| pmid = 22110167\n| issn = \n| volume = 208\n| issue = 13\n| pages = 2591\u20132598\n| last = Griffin\n| first = Daniel\n| first2=Thomas L. |last2=Rothstein\n| title = A small CD11b+ human B1 cell subpopulation stimulates T cells and is expanded in lupus\n| journal =  [[Journal of Experimental Medicine]]\n| date = December 2011\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1054/jcaf.2001.27829\n| pmid = 11782854\n| issn = \n| volume = 7\n| issue = 4\n| pages = 318-21\n| last = Anthony\n| first = Doing\n| first2=Daniel |last2=Griffin |first3=Jay A. |last3=Jacobson |first4=Ina J. |last4=Amber |first5=Edward |last5=Gilbert\n| title = B-cell function in chronic heart failure: Antibody response to pneumococcal vaccine\n| journal =  [[Journal of Cardiac Failure]]\n| date = 2011\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n==COVID-19 Response==\n\nGriffin has made a number of media appearances to offer stark warnings about the dangers to public health posed by the outbreak of the novel coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/health/can-you-catch-coronavirus-surfaces|title=Can you catch coronavirus from surfaces?|first=David|last=Aaro|date=March 18, 2020|website=Fox News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2020/04/02/825491635/think-youve-got-covid-19-here-s-what-doctors-say-about-when-to-seek-help|title=Think You've Got COVID-19? Here's What Doctors Say About When To Seek Help|website=NPR.org}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/hiking-beach-coronavirus/index.html|title=Is going to the beach OK? What about hiking?|first=Stacey |last=Lastoe|website=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5811061/drive-thru-coronavirus-testing-workers/|title=\u201cI Didn\u2019t Do a Good Enough Job Anticipating Demand.\u201d Hear From Health Care Workers Staffing Drive Thru COVID-19 Testing Centers|website=Time}}</ref> He has also covered the issue of ventilator shortages and the crucial role its supply plays in keeping severely-ill coronavirus patients alive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/04/01/coronavirus-what-is-a-ventilator-and-why-is-there-a-shortage/|title=Coronavirus: What is a ventilator and why is there a shortage?|first=Jackie|last=Salo|date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> Griffin also frequently appears on the scientific podcast \"This Week in Parasitism\" (TWiP) to educate lay audiences on the effects of the outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-595/|title=TWiV 595: Coronavirus update - Daniel Griffin MD in the parking lot &#124; This Week in Virology}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [https://parasiteswithoutborders.com/books/ Parasitic Diseases, 7th Edition]\n* [http://www.parasiteswithoutborders.com/ Parasites Without Borders]\n* [http://www.twiv.tv/TWIV This Week in Virology]\n* [https://www.microbe.tv/twip/ This Week in Parasitism]\n\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Griffin, Daniel}}\n[[Category:21st-century American biologists]]\n[[Category:American virologists]]\n[[Category:American textbook writers]]\n[[Category:American male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Columbia University faculty]]\n[[Category:New York University School of Medicine alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Daniel O. Griffin\n| image             = Dr._Daniel_Griffin.jpeg\n| image_size        = \n| caption           = Griffin in 2019\n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1967|7|15}}\n| birth_place       = [[New York City]], [[New York State]]{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n| death_date        = \n| death_place       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = American\n| nationality       = \n| ethnicity         = \n| fields            = [[Biochemistry]]<br>[[Molecular Biophysics]]<br>[[Public Health]]\n| workplaces        = [[Columbia University]] Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biophysics\n| alma_mater        = [[University of Colorado]] [[Bachelor of Arts|(B.A.)]] <br> [[New York University School of Medicine]] [[Doctorate of Medicine|(M.D.)]] <br>\n[[Elmezzi Graduate School of Molecular Medicine]] [[PhD|(Ph.D.)]]\n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| thesis_title      = \n| thesis_url        = \n| thesis_year       = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| known_for         = Tropical Diseases<br>HIV-1<br>\n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2012}}\n[[File:Vincent R., Dick D., Daniel G. at TWiP.jpg|thumb|Daniel O. Griffin with [[Vincent Racaniello]] and [[Dickson Despommier]] at the recording of the This Week in Parasitism (TWiP) podcast in 2015.]]\n\n'''Daniel O. Griffin''' (born July 15, 1967) {{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}is a member of the Division of Infectious Diseases and an Associate Research Scientist in the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biophysics at [[Columbia University]]. He also serves as the co-director of [[Parasites Without Borders]], a global nonprofit organization with a focus on those suffering from parasitic diseases in subtropical environments.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parasiteswithoutborders.com/|title=Home &#124; Parasites without Borders|date=April 3, 2018|website=parasiteswithoutborders.com}}</ref>\n\nGriffin focuses his research on [[HIV]], [[stem cells]] and the potential role that human B1 cells and natural antibodies play in the development of HIV-associated neoplasms.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asm.org/Biographies/Daniel-Griffin|title=Daniel Griffin|website=ASM.org}}</ref> As an expert in tropical diseases, his work also covers the clinical care of patients that reside in the [[New York metropolitan area]] as well as non-residents with a multitude of different infectious diseases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prohealthcare.com/locations-nav/providers/ny/daniel-griffin/1831125640.html|title=ProHEALTH|website=www.prohealthcare.com}}</ref> \n\nIn addition to teaching and supervising medical students and fellows at the [[Columbia University Medical Center]], Griffin is also actively involved in educating both medical and lay audiences on the internet. He is one of the hosts and a regular contributor to the highly popular scientific podcast \"This Week in Parasitism\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.microbe.tv/twip/about/|title=About TWiP &#124; This Week in Parasitism}}</ref> (TWiP) that was originally launched by [[Vincent Racaniello]] and [[Dickson Despommier]]. He is also one of the authors of [[Parasitic Diseases]], which is an established medical textbook dealing with basic and clinical aspects of infectious diseases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parasiteswithoutborders.com/books/|title=Books &#124; Parasites without Borders|date=February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Research==\n\nGriffin has research interest in the study of [[HIV-1]], malignancies, and stem cell latency as well as stem cell gene therapy utilizing retroviral vectors. He is the author of over 25 scientific publications.<ref>https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Daniel_Griffin2</ref>\n\n===Research publications===\n{{refbegin}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.4172/2155-6113.1000558\n| pmid =\n| issn = \n| volume = 7\n| issue = 4\n| pages = 1-3\n| last = Griffin\n| first = Daniel\n|first2=Michael J. |last2=Metzger |first3=Sheena |last3=Bharti |first4=Arif |last4=Dharsee |first5=Juan |last5=Carlos Rico |first6=Joseph |last6=McGowan\n| title = Co-infection with Hepatitis C Virus Increases Mortality in HIV-1 infected Patients through Increased Liver-Related Deaths Rather Than By Increasing Malignancy Related Deaths\n| journal = Journal of AIDS & Clinical Research\n| date = 2016\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1186/s12977-016-0246-0\n| pmid = 26945863\n| issn = \n| volume = 13\n| issue = 14\n| pages = \n| last = Griffin\n| first = Daniel\n| first2=Stephen P. |last2=Goff\n| title = Restriction of HIV-1-based lentiviral vectors in adult primary marrow-derived and peripheral mobilized human CD34+ hematopoietic stem and progenitor cells occurs prior to viral DNA integration\n| journal =  [[Retrovirology]]\n| date = March 2016\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.4172/2155-6113.1000532\n| pmid =\n| issn = 2155-6113\n| volume = 6\n| issue = 12\n| pages = \n| last = Rico\n| first = Juan Carlos\n|first2=Rebecca M. |last2=Schwartz |first3=Joseph |last3=McGowan |first4=Daniel |last4=Griffin \n| title = The Presence of a Malignant Comorbidity is a Significant Predictor of Increased 30-Day Hospital