\n| first = Daniel\n| first2=Thomas L. |last2=Rothstein\n| title = A small CD11b+ human B1 cell subpopulation stimulates T cells and is expanded in lupus\n| journal =  [[Journal of Experimental Medicine]]\n| date = December 2011\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| doi = 10.1054/jcaf.2001.27829\n| pmid = 11782854\n| issn = \n| volume = 7\n| issue = 4\n| pages = 318-21\n| last = Anthony\n| first = Doing\n| first2=Daniel |last2=Griffin |first3=Jay A. |last3=Jacobson |first4=Ina J. |last4=Amber |first5=Edward |last5=Gilbert\n| title = B-cell function in chronic heart failure: Antibody response to pneumococcal vaccine\n| journal =  [[Journal of Cardiac Failure]]\n| date = 2011\n| jstor = \n}}\n\n==COVID-19 Response==\n\nGriffin has made a number of media appearances to offer stark warnings about the dangers to public health posed by the outbreak of the novel coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/health/can-you-catch-coronavirus-surfaces|title=Can you catch coronavirus from surfaces?|first=David|last=Aaro|date=March 18, 2020|website=Fox News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2020/04/02/825491635/think-youve-got-covid-19-here-s-what-doctors-say-about-when-to-seek-help|title=Think You've Got COVID-19? Here's What Doctors Say About When To Seek Help|website=NPR.org}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/hiking-beach-coronavirus/index.html|title=Is going to the beach OK? What about hiking?|first=Stacey Lastoe|last=CNN|website=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5811061/drive-thru-coronavirus-testing-workers/|title=\u201cI Didn\u2019t Do a Good Enough Job Anticipating Demand.\u201d Hear From Health Care Workers Staffing Drive Thru COVID-19 Testing Centers|website=Time}}</ref> He has also covered the issue of ventilator shortages and the crucial role its supply plays in keeping severely-ill coronavirus patients alive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/04/01/coronavirus-what-is-a-ventilator-and-why-is-there-a-shortage/|title=Coronavirus: What is a ventilator and why is there a shortage?|first=Jackie|last=Salo|date=April 1, 2020}}</ref> Griffin also frequently appears on the scientific podcast \"This Week in Parasitism\" (TWiP) to educate lay audiences on the effects of the outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-595/|title=TWiV 595: Coronavirus update - Daniel Griffin MD in the parking lot &#124; This Week in Virology}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [https://parasiteswithoutborders.com/books/ Parasitic Diseases, 7th Edition]\n* [http://www.parasiteswithoutborders.com/ Parasites Without Borders]\n* [http://www.twiv.tv/TWIV This Week in Virology]\n* [https://www.microbe.tv/twip/ This Week in Parasitism]\n\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Griffin, Daniel}}\n[[Category:21st-century American biologists]]\n[[Category:American virologists]]\n[[Category:American textbook writers]]\n[[Category:American male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Columbia University faculty]]\n[[Category:New York University School of Medicine alumni]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed cite error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_O._Griffin"}
{"title_page": "Boxing at the 1960 Summer Olympics \u2013 Bantamweight", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic boxing tournament}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Bantamweight boxing\n|games = 1960 Summer\n|image = \n|caption = \n|venue = [[PalaLottomatica|Palazzo dello Sport]]\n|dates = 25 August \u2013 5 September\n|competitors = 32\n|nations = 32\n|gold = [[Oleg Grigoryev]]\n|goldNOC = URS\n|silver = [[Primo Zamparini]]\n|silverNOC = ITA\n|bronze = [[Brunon Bendig]]\n|bronzeNOC = POL\n|bronze2 = [[Oliver Taylor (boxer)|Oliver Taylor]]\n|bronzeNOC2 = AUS\n|prev=[[Boxing at the 1956 Summer Olympics \u2013 Bantamweight|1956]]\n|next=[[Boxing at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Bantamweight|1964]]\n}}\n{{Boxing at the 1960 Summer Olympics}}\nThe '''men's bantamweight''' event was part of the [[Boxing at the 1960 Summer Olympics|boxing programme]] at the [[1960 Summer Olympics]].  The weight class allowed boxers of up to 54 kilograms to compete. The competition was held from 25 August to 5 September 1960. 32 boxers from 32 nations competed.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1960/BOX/mens-bantamweight.html |title=Boxing at the 1960 Rome Summer Games: Men's Bantamweight |work=Sports Reference |accessdate=25 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Competition format==\n\nThe competition was a straight single-elimination tournament, with no bronze medal match (two bronze medals were awarded, one to each semifinal loser). There were 33 boxers entered, but the boxer from the [[Republic of China (Formosa) at the 1960 Summer Olympics|Republic of China]] withdrew at the last minute, too late to change the bracket; therefore, one bout was conducted in the round of 64 and one boxer received a bye in the round of 32.\n\n==Results==\n[[File:Oliver Taylor, Brunon Bendig, Oleg Grigoryev, Primo Zamparini 1960.jpg |thumb|Left-right: Oliver Taylor, Brunon Bendig, Oleg Grigoryev, Primo Zamparini]]\n\nResults of 